8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to S.P. 13,
9 L.D. 4, “An Act to Adopt Eastern Standard Time Year-round”
10 Amend the amendment in subsection 4 in the last line (page 1, line 13 in amendment)
11 by striking out the following: "at 2 a.m. on the 2nd Sunday of March 2026" and inserting
12 the following: 'when New Hampshire enacts and effectuates legislation establishing eastern
13 standard time as the standard time year-round for that state'
14 Amend the amendment by inserting before the 2nd instructional paragraph the
15 following:
16 'Amend the bill by inserting after section 2 the following:
17 'Sec. 3. Notification of New Hampshire's observance of eastern standard
18 time year-round. The Secretary of State shall notify the Secretary of the Senate, the
19 Clerk of the House of Representatives and the Revisor of Statutes when New Hampshire
20 enacts and effectuates legislation establishing eastern standard time as the standard time
21 for that state as provided in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 1, section 151, subsection 4.'
22 '
23 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
24 section number to read consecutively.
25 SUMMARY
2266 This amendment provides that year-round eastern standard time for the State takes
2277 effect when New Hampshire enacts and effectuates legislation establishing eastern standard
2288 time as the standard time year-round for that state. It requires the Secretary of State to
2299 notify the Secretary of the Senate, the Clerk of the House of Representatives and the
3300 Revisor of Statutes when New Hampshire enacts and effectuates such legislation.
